<p><strong>The minimum effective frequency is once per week.</strong> Anything less and your profile risks looking abandoned to both Google and potential customers.</p>
<p>GBP posts used to expire after 7 days and disappear from your profile. Google changed this in late 2025. Posts now remain visible in your Updates section indefinitely. However, Google still prioritizes recent posts in search results and the <a href="/glossary/local-pack/">local pack</a>. A post from 3 months ago carries far less weight than one from yesterday.</p>
<p>This is why consistency matters more than volume. Three posts per week, every week, beats 10 posts in one week followed by 3 weeks of silence.</p>
